#originalStanceText=Yes
#originalTopic=should-marriage-for-same-sex-couples-be-legal
Imagine a social contract entitled "married with a man".  Imagine a man (who can give legal consent) being unable to enter such a social contract.  Under these very limited circumstances, is it not true that the man is being discriminated against on the basis of gender?Granted, marriages are more complicated than other social contracts, perhaps...